Import .xlsx data based on read_excel readxl

ok.data.function.excel_xlsx.Rd

Import .xlsx data based on read_excel readxl

ok.data.function.excel_xlsx(
  input_dataFile,
  input_column_names,
  input_trim_spaces,
  input_range_specified_bol,
  input_range_specs,
  input_worksheet_specified_bol,
  input_worksheet_specs,
  input_dataFile_datapath,
  input_rows_to_skip
)

Arguments

input_dataFile

shiny-related dataFile object
input_column_names

TRUE to use the first row as column names, FALSE to get default names
input_trim_spaces

Should leading and trailing whitespace be trimmed?
input_range_specified_bol

boolean to indicate if range should be specified
input_range_specs

A cell range to read from. See documentation ?read_xlsx
input_worksheet_specified_bol

boolean to indicate if worksheet should be specified
input_worksheet_specs

Sheet to read. See documentation ?read_xlsx
input_dataFile_datapath

datapath
input_rows_to_skip

Minimum number of rows to skip before reading anything. Default is 0

Value
